Human Rights Watch employs researchers who work in the field to investigate human rights conditions in over 80 countries around the world. Incorporating interviews with victims of abuse as well as local advocates, journalists, and officials, Human Rights Watch&rsquo;s studies provide up-to-date information to world leaders across an immense range of human rights topics. Human Rights Watch reports have been cited in the press, as well as government and United Nations findings. These documentations lead the legal and moral groundwork for important change. The ultimate goal is for human rights abusers to be brought to justice through government intervention and sanctions that do not target those who are affected by crisis.
&nbsp;
Human Rights Watch is a four-star charity on Charity Navigator, the highest rating possible. They are also a Better Business Bureau accredited charity.&nbsp;

